HEADWORD: Tachistoscope
<hw>Ta*chis"to*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ta`chistos</grk>, superl. of <grk>tachy`s</grk> swift +
<ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An apparatus for
exposing briefly to view a screen bearing letters or figures. It is used
in studying the range of attention, or the power of distinguishing
separate objects in a single impression.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tachograph</ent>⟦br⟧
